name: Apricot toned birdy bag
description:
Here’s another of my handmade totes, featuring a mix of modern designer fabric, featuring birds. 
I think it’s rather “tweet”!

name: Clown water jug
description: This is a fab reclaimed vintage item, in pristine used condition. Made in Malaysia by Technicware, measuring 17.5 cm high, including removable lid.  Features clown transfer on both sides, and is waiting for you to adopt it and add to your 70’s retro kitchen cupboard.

name: Saucy Suzy Apples tote
description:
Here’s one of my most recent bag creations, Saucy Suzy and her basket of apples, as part of my Clever with a Needle retro range.

	Suzy is hand embroidered by me and then appliqued onto a handmade tote bag featuring 1930’s style vintage fabric.  Perfect for toting around your books, shopping, or indeed, your apples!

name: Vintage shoes
description:
I don’t want to part with them really, but my big feet mean I can’t wear them! Sigh!

	These are a gorgeous pair of brown leather shoes with black patent leather detail, made in Australia by Footrest.  From the logo design, I’d say about 1970’s…I wonder if the design was influenced by the 30’s revival in fashion of that decade (the result of the film version of ‘The Great Gatsby’)?  To me they have a very 30’s feel about them.

	They are size 7D and measure approx 25 cm from toe to heel.  They have some scuffing on the toes, but are well made from quality materials, so the lucky peson with size 7 feet will get a lot of wear out of them.

	If you’d like more pics or details, please contact me.

name: Holly Hobby bud vase
description:
Here’s a little Holly Hobby vase, mearsing 8.5 cm high, with a 4 cm base.  She’s carrying her kitty and the caption reads “A true friend is the best possession”. It’s in excellent condition, with no chips or cracks, but has been used as inside the vase has some brown discolouration, but given the small neck, you can’t see it when the piece is on display.  The base is stamped as per my photo, and is dated 1974.

	This one is slightly hard to part with, as I remember that my friend from primary school gave me a dish with the same design for my 6th birthday…I don’t know where the dish or the friend is now.   But I need to share, so if you’re a Holly Hobby fan, you’ll love it!
